import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['delay'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.boxplot(data['distance'])
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(y=data['distance'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median distance')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['origin', 'destination']).size().reset_index(name='counts')
    data = data.sort_values(by='counts', ascending=False).head(10)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax.bar(data['origin'] + ' to ' + data['destination'], data['counts'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Route')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Flights')
    ax.set_title('Which airports have the highest number of flights?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y%m%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['delay'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of flight delays over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['delay', 'distance']]
    plt.scatter(data['distance'], data['delay'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Distance')
    plt.ylabel('Delay')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between distance and delay?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
